  "time_ut": 1661424231,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1  \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranjan will be released tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tourism Minister Harin Fernando has said that former Member of Parliament of United People's Power Ranjan Ramanayake will be released tomorrow or on Monday the 27th.",
        "Minister Harin Fernando posted a post on his Facebook website in this regard.",
        "The minister said that a request has been made to President Ranil Wickremesinghe to release former Member of Parliament Ranjan Ramanayake.",
        "Minister Fernando said that Minister Manusha Nanayakkara and himself have made this request.",
        "In this case, former Member of Parliament Ranjan Ramanayake, who is serving a sentence for contempt of court, has today (25) submitted an affidavit to the court seeking forgiveness for making comments that discredit the judiciary.",
        "On August 21, 2017, Ranjan Ramanayake had made comments insulting the judiciary outside Alarimalika. Stating that his comments had undermined faith in the country's judiciary, Sinhala Ravya Organization secretary Magalkanthe Sudatta Thera and retired Air Force officer Agiyor had filed a case in the High Court.",
        "After examining this, the High Court sentenced Ranjan Ramanayake to four years of rigorous imprisonment for contempt of court and sentenced him on January 12, 2021. So far, Ramanayake's sentence has completed one year and seven months.",
        "He has admitted that the comment he made outside Alarimalika was completely false, not only defamatory but also insulting the entire judiciary, and he has mentioned in his affidavit that he apologizes to the entire judiciary in this regard.",
        "Moreover, he has also apologized for the opinion he issued on August 21, 2017 outside the High Court premises saying that he will not take it back.",
        "Also, he has also promised in his affidavit that during his lifetime, he will not publish any opinion that criticizes or discredits the judiciary as a whole.",
        "Ranjan Ramanayake, former Member of Parliament of United People's Shakti, who is serving a prison sentence, had recently signed the papers for a presidential amnesty."
      ],
